history.text: What did you think of the reviews given to Zootopia?
I thought the review given to Zootopia was right on the money.
I think it was a little over the top in terms of reviews. I think I would of given it a 7 overall
I respectfully disagree, because where else would you hear a story of a rabbit as a police officer?
For that as well as the message of looking past species stereotypes, I would give the movie at least 9 out of 10 stars.
It's not the story, that I felt was over the top. It was the reviews overall. I think rotten tomatoes can be a bit biased with certain films
Yes, I agree that rotten tomatoes is a very biased website, but overall they actually hit it right out of the park with this one.
Story-wise I think it was decent but it's been done before. What did you tink of the story?

I thought that the story was very good, and that even though it's not believable that a rabbit would be a police officer, the underlying message of looking past species stereotypes as well as hurtful assumptions is something that we could use in our culture today.
I would agree with that, I did like the subtle nod to race relations. I think it was well written into the movie overall. How did you like the animation itself?
